content.text:
Determining the type of security control assessment;
Determining the security controls and control enhancements to be included in the assessment;
Selecting the appropriate assessment procedures to be used during the assessment based on security controls and control enhancements in the system security plan;
Tailoring the selected assessment procedures for the information system impact level and organization's operating environment;
Developing additional assessment procedures, if necessary, to address other security controls and control enhancements;
Developing a strategy to apply the extended assessment procedure;
Optimizing assessment procedures to reduce duplication of effort and provide cost-effective assessment solutions; and
Finalizing the assessment plan and obtaining the approvals needed for its execution.
